   "body" : "Would it be possible to change the maximum number of orphan blocks kept in memory from a constant (MAX_ORPHAN_BLOCKS = 750) to a startup parameter -maxorphanblocks, defaulting to the current value?\r\n\r\n750 average sized blocks (without any overhead) amount to >210 MB at the moment, which I've found to be too much for 512 MB RAM (e.g. a Raspberry Pi). And the Bitcoin network needs more full nodes, no?",
